# Firestore schema reference

This app reads from shared Firestore collections (`vendors`, `vendor_spend`) whose schemas are owned by the agent service.

- **Canonical schema docs:** `../agent/docs/architecture.md` (sections "Firestore `vendors` schema" and "Firestore `vendor_spend` schema")
- **Sync scripts** (write-side): `../agent/service/sync_billcom_spend.py`, `../agent/service/sync_billcom.py`
- **Query helpers** (read-side): `../agent/service/firestore_client.py`

When building frontend features that read these collections, consult those files directly rather than asking the user to describe the schema.

## Quick reference

### `vendors` collection
One doc per vendor. Fields include: `id`, `name`, `billcomId`, `nameLower`, `paymentMethod`, `accountType`, `track1099`, `owner`, `department`, `purpose`, `spendType`, `hide`, `billingFrequency`, contract fields, `toolCall`, `lastSyncedAt`.

### `vendor_spend` collection
One doc per vendor per month. Doc ID: `{vendorId}_{YYYY-MM}`.
Core fields: `vendorId`, `vendorName`, `month` (YYYY-MM), `totalAmount`, `billCount`, `toolCall`, `lastSyncedAt`.
Denormalized from vendor doc: `paymentMethod`, `billingFrequency`, `department`, `owner`, `track1099`, `accountType`, `purpose`, `spendType`, `hide`.
